  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The applicable requirement is ASME V&V 40-2018 Section 6 MRL-5 acceptance threshold for hemolysis QoI; a Requirement object capturing this threshold is embedded in the evidence package narrative and referenced by the validation results, but the top-level bindsRequirement link is not carried on the UnitOfAssurance node itself, consistent with the Minimal profile binding rules. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across 5 flow-speed combinations. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). Decision: Accepted at Minimal profile threshold.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
